STANDARDS FOR NETWORK VALIDATIONS FOR GNS PLAYERS


THE GNS NETWORK INVOLVES DIFFERENT TOOLS PROVIDING DIFFERENT NETWORK
FUNCTIONS RANGING FROM TROUBLE TICKET RECORDING, SYSTEM DIAGNOSTICS,
HOST/NODE STATUS MONITORING TO CODE GENERATION AND CODE LOADING.
THOSE FUNCTIONS ARE CARRIED OUT BY DIFFERENT OPERATORS FROM DIFFERENT AREAS,
FROM DIFFERENT BT TYMNET DIVISIONS AND ALSO FROM OTHER COMPANIES SUCH AS
MCDONNELL DOUGLAS.
THOSE OPERATORS ARE TO BE STRINGENTLY GRANTED WITH THE ACCESS LEVEL TO THOSE
FUNCTIONS ACCORDING TO THEIR NETWORK ROLES.
THIS IS MANDATORY TO THE NETWORK SECURITY.
IN ORDER TO GUARANTEE THE RIGHT ACCESS ARE GIVEN TO THE RIGHT PLAYER,
STANDARDS FOR NETWORK VALIDATIONS MUST BE DEFINED.
BELOW ARE STANDARDS ONLY FOR EUROPEAN GNS PLAYERS.

TYPES OF NETWORK VALIDATIONS

BASED ON THE DIFFERENT NETWORK TOOLS, THERE ARE 4 TYPES   OF   NETWORK
VALIDATIONS: ACCESS TO PAPER SYSTEM 56, ACCESS FOR MAINTENANCE, ACCESS FOR
MONITORING, AND ACCESS FOR CODE GENERATION AND LOADING.

1. PAPER SYSTEM 56

   1.1 NETWORK USERNAME WITH TICKET-CREATION PRIVILEDGE.

       THIS POWERFUL USERNAME IS ONLY FOR BT.
       EACH COUNTRY HAS ITS OWN USERNAME
       IT IS ASSIGNED ONLY TO ALLOWED PERSONNEL HAVING BEEN TRAINED ON PAPER.
       IT ALLOW THE USER TO CREATE A TICKET FOR A NETWORK PROBLEM BY ENTERING
       INFORMATION IN PAPER SYSTEM DIRECTLY WITH A REQUEST-TO-OPEN STATUS
       THEN FORWARD IT FOR VALIDATION WITH A TICKET-OPENED STATUS STARTING
       THE ESCALATION TIMERS.
       ( OTHER PEOPLE HAVING ONLY ACCESS TO ENTER STATUSES WITH THEIR OWN 
         USERNAMES OR USERNAMES DEFINED FOR MAINTENANCE PURPOSES )

   1.2 PAPER ID

       EACH SUPPORT GROUP HAS ITS PAPER ID IN THE PAPER SYSTEM
       THE PAPER ID WILL BE THE CONTROLLED GROUP OF A TICKET IF THE SUPPORT
       GROUP IS THE OWNER OF THE TICKET
       THE PAPER ID WILL BE THE DEFERRED GROUP OF A TICKET IF THE SUPPORT
       GROUP HAS BEEN REQUESTED TO TAKE ACTION FOR RESOLVING THE TICKET
       FOR EACH COUNTRY, MCDONNELL DOUGLAS FIELD SERVICE IS ASSIGNED WITH
       A SEPARATE PAPER ID.

2. MAINTENANCE

       EACH COUNTRY HAS ITS OWN MAINTENANCE USERNAME.
       THE SUGGESTED USERNAME FORMAT IS BTM+'COUNTRY ID' ( COUNTRY ID
       IS FOR INSTANCE UK FOR UK, FR FOR FRANCE ETC... ).
       THE USERNAME MUST BE DEFINED IN THE NODE GOODGUY-LIST FOR
       NODES LOCATED IN THE COUNTRY IN ADDITION TO A GENERIC USERNAME
       XXXX.
       THE USERNAME HAS ALSO ACCESS TO A MUX HOST SET UP FOR EUROPEAN 
       GNS PLAYERS, TO THE PAPER SYSTEM 56, TO ALL NETWORK GATEWAYS 
       HOSTS ( X75 , X25 OR TYMNET T201 ), AS WELL AS TO INTERFACE 
       OPERATION MANAGER ( XOM, TOM, BOM, ETC.... FOR INTERFACES SUCH AS
PAGE 1-2			VALIDA.STD     THU 27-JUL-95 10:27

       XCOM AND TYMCOM, THE USERNAME MUST BE SPECIFIED IN SLOT FILE
       IN ADDITION TO THE OTHER OPERATOR USERNAME USED BY GLOBAL NETWORK
       SUPPORT PERSONNEL SUCH AS STS ).
       IT'S RECOMMENDED TO DISTINGUISH THIS USERNAME FROM THE USERNAME
